 <purpose>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of state.
 
The state definition module identifies a type of state by specifying the criterium that shall be satisified for 
something to be in a state of that type. 
<eg>A state definition that is defined by the presence of an identified fault in a product.</eg> 
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
 <li>definition of state</li> 
 <li>definition of what is needed for a state to exist</li> 
 <li>relationship between two or more states</li>  
 <li>relationship between a state and the product, activity, people or organization that it affects</li>  
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
 <li>behaviour or history of product data capable of having state</li> 
 <li>individual state</li> 
 </outscope>

